Jeanette Chabalala, News24(File, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Kimberley &ndash; The chopped up body of a woman was on Friday&nbsp;found in&nbsp;a shallow grave at Soul City in Galeswewe, Northern Cape police said. &nbsp;A 39-year-old man, believed to be the woman&rsquo;s partner, was arrested shortly after the gruesome discovery, said Lieutenant Olebogeng Tawana. &nbsp;He said the arrest came after an intensive search,&nbsp;in partnership with the local councillor and community members. &nbsp;Tawana said the body was found stashed in a carry bag in a shallow grave in an open field. &nbsp;"On the April 17, the man reported his partner as a missing person at Kagisho police station. He informed the police that he last saw her on April 13," said Tawana. &nbsp; &nbsp;The man&nbsp;was expected to appear in the Galeshewe Magistrate&rsquo;s Court on May 3. &nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.